'''Orlando Mosquera''' (born 25 December 1994), commonly known as '''Kuty Mosquera''',<ref>[https://www.critica.com.pa/deportes/portero-orlando-cuti-mosquera-jugara-en-primera-division-de-israel-453063 Portero Orlando ‘Cuti’ Mosquera jugará en Primera División de Israel] critica.com.pa</ref> is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Fayha FC|Al-Fayha]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Career==
On 1 November 2015, Mosquera scored to tie Tauro 2-2 during the 90th minute. After that, he played for Tauro, helping them win the 2017 Panamanian top flight Clasura as well as the 2018 and 2019 Aperturas.<ref>[https://www.prensa.com/deportes/orlando-mosquera-la-muralla-mas-valiosa-del-tauro-fc-campeon/ Orlando Mosquera, la muralla más valiosa del Tauro FC campeón] prensa.com</ref>

For the second half of 2019/20, he signed for Boluspor in the Turkish second division.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/deportes/futbol/Orlando-Kuty-MosqueraLa-cuarentena-Turquia_0_1349865536.html|title=Orlando 'Kuty' Mosquera:"La cuarentena en Turquía ha sido regular"|date=27 April 2020 |publisher=rpctv.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jmdeportes.com/futbol/kuty-mosquera-figura-clave-para-lograr-objetivo-de-su-club/|title=¡»KUTY» MOSQUERA FIGURA CLAVE PARA LOGRAR OBJETIVO DE SU CLUB!|date=19 July 2020 |publisher=jmdeportes.com}}</ref> In 2021, he signed for [[Club Always Ready|Always Ready]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportbolivia.com/mosquera-la-muralla-de-always-que-se-enfoca-en-el-campeonato/|title=Mosquera, la muralla de Always que se enfoca en el "campeonato"|publisher=sportbolivia.com (Archived)|access-date=8 September 2023|archive-date=2 May 2022|archive-url=https://archive.today/20220502191446/https://sportbolivia.com/mosquera-la-muralla-de-always-que-se-enfoca-en-el-campeonato/|url-status=bot: unknown}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cospanama.com/invencible-el-panameno-orlando-mosquera-suma-8-porterias-cero-el-always-ready-boliviano-n5572237|title=el panameño Orlando Mosquera suma 8 porterías en cero con el Always Ready boliviano|date=26 October 2021 |publisher=cospanama.com}}</ref> In 2022, he signed for [[Carabobo F.C.|Carabobo]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ligafutve.org/orlando-mosquera-impone-su-competitividad-en-el-carabobo/|title=ORLANDO MOSQUERA IMPONE SU COMPETITIVIDAD EN EL CARABOBO|date=10 May 2022 |publisher=ligafutve.org}}</ref> In early 2023, he signed for [[Monagas SC|Monagas]] and after a successful [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup|Gold Cup]] for Panama in the summer of that year, he got a move to [[Maccabi Tel Aviv]] in the later stages of the summer 2023 transfer window

